50|$|In 1954, United Airlines {{became the}} first airline to {{purchase}} modern <b>flight</b> <b>simulators</b> which had visual, sound, and motion cues for training pilots. Purchased for 3 million (1954) from Curtiss-Wright, these were the first of today's modern <b>flight</b> <b>simulators</b> for training of commercial passenger aircraft pilots.|$|R
