40|$|In this paper, {{we present}} the {{structural}} modeling approach, an application framework and development {{process for the}} construction of <b>flight</b> <b>simulators.</b> Structural modeling was developed to address functional, nonfunctional, and process requirements for <b>flight</b> <b>simulators.</b> It has been successfully used in the development of large scale (one million lines of Ada code) <b>flight</b> <b>simulators</b> for the United States Air Force. A structural model promotes a simple and coherent software architecture with a small number of specialized structural elements obeying a few systemwide coordination strategies. It is this simplicity coherence of the software architecture that enables analysis to demonstrate the quality of the system...|$|R
